This article is a transcript of President Biden's remarks at a ceremony honoring 15 public safety officers with the Medal of Valor, the highest award a President can bestow on a public safety officer. The President expressed gratitude for the officers' leadership and recognized their exceptional courage and selflessness in saving lives. He also acknowledged the sacrifices made by the families of the fallen officers and expressed condolences to those who lost loved ones in the line of duty. The President highlighted the importance of law enforcement and firefighting as essential parts of American communities and praised the honorees for their extraordinary heroism. He awarded the medals to each recipient and commended them for reflecting the best part of America.